The paper deals with interference management in wireless small cell networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves optimizing delay-rate tradeoff, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT). The problem is formulated as a noncooperative game, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT). The proposed approach is distributed and involves autonomous decision-making, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulation results, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
